java/io/netty/util/Recycler.java#L300\r\n\r\nIn the ideal scenario of a pool which has already N elements in (recycled afer a burst of usage - yet to verify how much realistic can be this), if a new claim and release happen on a pooled element, the release will move the released element by the end of the `ArrayDeque`, meaning that a subsequent claim *won't* pick it again, but the next in line recycled element instead, wasting some precious cache locality effect.\r\n\r\nTurning the `ArrayDeque` in an `ArrayList` used as a stack can be a better option, but require some benchmarking to verify that is a valid improvement.","closed_by":{"login":"normanmaurer","id":439362,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzOTM2Mg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/439362?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer","html_url":"https://github.com/normanmaurer","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/netty/netty/issues/14268/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/netty/netty/issues/14268/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}